body: Would be useful and provide an easy means to support module discovery in jqwik.

In the meantime, you could resort to temporarily use the "unsupported" `findAllClassesInModule` in [ModuleUtils](https://github.com/junit-team/junit5/blob/master/junit-platform-commons/src/main/java/org/junit/platform/commons/util/ModuleUtils.java#L96) method, though.
Just noticed that - unlike the Methods in ReflectionSupport - `ModuleUtils.findAllClassesInModule` does not have a classNamefilter predicate as parameter. Any reason for this asymmetry?

Added the current snapshot version of **net.jqwik** to the `junit5-vanilla-modules` sample via https://github.com/junit-team/junit5-samples/commit/8398dd5136c3c7630ccac93b9982b831e87958c4

See the test plan run tree at https://travis-ci.org/junit-team/junit5-samples/jobs/347992083#L647
